fire-fly
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A tent-fly used to keep the campfire and its environs dry in wet weather. A special tent-fly used esp. to keep the campfire, and its surrounds, dry in wet weather. Cf fly.
Origin:
